<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-24T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-24T21:00:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/971a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-24T22:00:00-04:00">November
                                    24, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1690. For Adler from the Secretary of the Treasury.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Mr. Hsi Te-mou and Mr. T. L. Soong have informed the Treasury that
                                Dr. Kung agrees with the Treasury that under present circumstances
                                the 1941 Agreement should not be renewed.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>The Treasury herewith instructs you to submit your resignation to
                                Dr. Kung as of December 31, although at your discretion you may
                                postpone date of resignation until January 31, 1944, if you feel
                                that additional month may be necessary to wind up Board’s affairs.
                                [Morgenthau.]</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>